      "text": [
        "هِ اَلْجِيفَةُ قَالَ «يُتَوَضَّأُ مِنَ اَلْجَانِبِ اَلْآخَرِ وَ لاَ يُتَوَضَّأُ مِنْ جَانِبِ اَلْجِيفَةِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.21 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about stagnant water that contains a dead animal.\nImam (as) said: \"Perform ablution from the other side and not from the side where the dead animal is\"."
        ]
      }
